        "body": "<p>Yes, You can use Java streams to solve this, Try this code in your code :<\/p>\n<pre><code>List&lt;Customer&gt; customersWithAllItems = customers.stream()\n            .filter(customer -&gt; {\n        List&lt;String&gt; customerItemNames = customer.getCartItems().stream()\n            .map(item -&gt; item.getItemId().split(&quot;-&quot;)[1]) \n            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n        List&lt;String&gt; masterItemNames = masterListItems.stream()\n            .map(Item::getItemName)\n            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n        return masterItemNames.containsAll(customerItemNames);\n    })\n            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
